OL,5, A former football club chairman has    
OL,6, been found guilty of fraud in a #3.9m  
OL,7, spread betting "Ponzi" scheme.         
OL,9,FChristopher Toynton, 73, was convicted 
OL,10,Ffollowing a two-month trial at Lincoln 
OL,11,FCrown Court.                           
OL,13,FThe court heard investors lost money on
OL,14,Fthe scheme, which was named the Lottery
OL,15,FSyndicate Club.                        
OL,17,FToynton, the ex-chairman of Spalding   
OL,18,FUnited, will be sentenced later        
OL,19,Falongside accountant Ross Gibson who   
OL,20,Fpleaded guilty to three charges.       
